est design, indicating it’s not an environment issue, but is related to using the ML-DSA key. I’m considering whether we should provide guidance, perhaps suggesting \\\"advisory_preparation\\\" within the agent guidance.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering agent guidance setup**\\n\\nI'm reflecting on the situation where meaningful coverage can be reached without external services, which leads me to conclude that we should go with \\\"no_action.\\\" However, if there's any agent guidance, it could clarify that no environment or system properties are needed when covering ML-DSA. I think it’s important to highlight risks, especially regarding JDK-specific issues and avoiding synthetic ML-DSA. If we choose \\\"no_action,\\\" I wonder what the role of non-empty agent guidance would be.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "{\n  \"action\": \"no_action\",\n  \"summary\": \"netty-pkitesting is a self-contained Netty test-support artifact for generating X.509 certificates and CRLs. Its required Bouncy Castle dependencies are declared transitively, and normal meaningful coverage is reachable without extra Maven dependencies, Docker services, or environment/system properties.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"No environment variables or system properties are required. For JDK-version-sensitive post-quantum algorithms such as ML-DSA/ML-KEM, tests should gate coverage with the library's Algorithm.isSupported()/supportSigning() checks or use standard RSA/EC paths; synthetic keys reporting algorithm ML-DSA can trigger java.security.AsymmetricKey reflection failures on runtimes where that JDK type is unavailable.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"ML-DSA/ML-KEM behavior is JDK-dependent and may differ across JDK 24/25 and earlier runtimes.\",\n    \"RevocationServer starts an in-process loopback HttpServer on a random local port, but it does not require Docker or external network infrastructure.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_037b21f448606816016a3e942286cc8194bb342cbfdf6f23b5\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 2106, "output": 756, "cacheRead": 28160, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 31022, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782486039462, "responseId": "resp_037b21f448606816016a3e9417ee348194bee89f36b65c9c5e"}}
